1
00:00:43,410 --> 00:00:44,500
Be careful.

2
00:00:45,250 --> 00:00:47,580
-He's strong.
-Got it.

3
00:00:49,090 --> 00:00:53,090
Wh… What is going on
so early in the morning?

4
00:00:58,010 --> 00:01:01,060
It doesn't seem like anyone's here.

5
00:01:01,640 --> 00:01:04,270
I can't tell with all this junk.

6
00:01:04,350 --> 00:01:07,480
Throw everything out!

7
00:01:10,150 --> 00:01:13,530
Jeez, what is this all about?

8
00:01:15,450 --> 00:01:16,530
He escaped.

9
00:01:17,030 --> 00:01:20,160
-What?
-Gardar escaped.

10
00:01:20,660 --> 00:01:24,370
Is there any other reason why
they would be ransacking our shed?

11
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:32,340
Arnheid!

12
00:03:34,580 --> 00:03:36,040
Wait, Einar!

13
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:40,300
Stop for a second. Einar!

14
00:03:41,380 --> 00:03:43,010
If Gardar escaped,

15
00:03:43,090 --> 00:03:45,800
he will definitely
try to find Arnheid again.

16
00:03:48,140 --> 00:03:50,480
What will you do once you're with Arnheid?

17
00:03:51,100 --> 00:03:53,140
Are you going to chase Gardar away?

18
00:03:56,690 --> 00:03:57,860
I don't know.

19
00:03:58,900 --> 00:03:59,900
But…

20
00:04:01,490 --> 00:04:02,450
there must be

21
00:04:02,950 --> 00:04:04,820
something that

22
00:04:04,910 --> 00:04:07,160
I can do to help Arnheid!

23
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:31,980
Arnheid!

24
00:04:38,020 --> 00:04:39,520
That's not him.

25
00:04:39,610 --> 00:04:41,570
It's not Gardar.

26
00:04:41,650 --> 00:04:42,990
It's two slaves.

27
00:04:44,490 --> 00:04:47,530
What were their names…?

28
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:50,030
Oh, they work for the master…

29
00:04:51,410 --> 00:04:53,500
Thorfinn and Einar?

30
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,120
Yes, that's right.

31
00:04:56,210 --> 00:04:58,130
What are they here for?

32
00:04:59,540 --> 00:05:02,300
What should we do, Boss?
Should we chase them away?

33
00:05:04,470 --> 00:05:06,260
No, don't mind them.

34
00:05:06,760 --> 00:05:08,850
Let them be.

35
00:05:21,610 --> 00:05:22,610
Um…

36
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:24,690
Arnheid.

37
00:05:27,410 --> 00:05:28,280
Yes…

38
00:05:29,660 --> 00:05:31,700
It's about Gardar, right?

39
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:34,700
You knew?

40
00:05:38,750 --> 00:05:39,630
Yes.

41
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:43,250
I…

42
00:05:44,460 --> 00:05:45,800
let him escape.

43
00:05:47,510 --> 00:05:48,680
I cut

44
00:05:49,550 --> 00:05:50,970
Gardar's rope.

45
00:05:54,970 --> 00:05:56,100
Gardar

46
00:05:56,850 --> 00:05:58,270
killed the guard.

47
00:05:59,060 --> 00:06:01,610
And I thought we were

48
00:06:02,770 --> 00:06:04,820
both going to die.

49
00:06:06,610 --> 00:06:07,610
I…

50
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,410
After that,

51
00:06:18,790 --> 00:06:21,250
the other guards

52
00:06:21,830 --> 00:06:22,790
rushed out

53
00:06:24,210 --> 00:06:25,510
but Gardar

54
00:06:26,670 --> 00:06:27,970
killed them all.

55
00:06:33,140 --> 00:06:34,720
The guards again…

56
00:06:35,220 --> 00:06:37,890
This is bad… really bad.

57
00:06:43,310 --> 00:06:44,230
Einar.

58
00:06:45,110 --> 00:06:47,150
The guards are watching us.

59
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:49,280
Act like you're helping with the dishes

60
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:51,160
and get closer to Arnheid.

61
00:06:58,540 --> 00:06:59,660
Stay calm

62
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:02,500
and tell us what the situation is.

63
00:07:06,130 --> 00:07:08,510
During the fight,

64
00:07:09,010 --> 00:07:11,550
Gardar also suffered a bad injury.

65
00:07:13,010 --> 00:07:16,390
Then the two of us ran away in the rain

66
00:07:17,770 --> 00:07:20,020
until we got to the old master's house.

67
00:07:21,690 --> 00:07:22,600
But

68
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:25,020
while I was treating his wound,

69
00:07:25,110 --> 00:07:27,440
Gardar lost consciousness.

70
00:07:28,780 --> 00:07:31,280
He was so heavy and I couldn't carry him.

71
00:07:31,860 --> 00:07:32,740
But

72
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:36,330
I was somehow able to hide him.

73
00:07:37,700 --> 00:07:40,410
So Gardar is here?

74
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:41,960
Yes.

75
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:46,500
The old master helped us out.

76
00:07:47,170 --> 00:07:50,800
Snake and his men came right after that.

77
00:07:52,510 --> 00:07:53,760
They seem to think

78
00:07:54,510 --> 00:07:56,260
that Gardar escaped

79
00:07:56,350 --> 00:07:59,600
and is hiding somewhere.

80
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:03,310
They're in the main house

81
00:08:03,810 --> 00:08:07,320
waiting for Gardar to come and see me.

82
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:10,860
Snake and two other men.

83
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:15,320
Why…?

84
00:08:15,950 --> 00:08:18,620
Why did you do something
so dangerous on your own?

85
00:08:19,540 --> 00:08:21,200
You said you'd let the storm pass

86
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:23,830
for the sake of your child!

87
00:08:31,550 --> 00:08:34,050
Why…?

88
00:08:43,850 --> 00:08:45,100
A dream…

89
00:08:46,810 --> 00:08:47,860
I couldn't help

90
00:08:48,690 --> 00:08:51,030
but dream, I guess.

91
00:08:52,070 --> 00:08:53,820
About my unborn child,

92
00:08:54,450 --> 00:08:55,780
Gardar,

93
00:08:56,990 --> 00:08:58,740
and our family…

94
00:09:00,490 --> 00:09:01,700
I thought

95
00:09:02,370 --> 00:09:05,670
that maybe things were back to normal.

96
00:09:09,210 --> 00:09:10,340
Back to…

97
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:12,550
Back to normal.

98
00:09:18,930 --> 00:09:20,220
His eyes

99
00:09:21,010 --> 00:09:24,560
used to be filled with so much confidence.

100
00:09:25,060 --> 00:09:27,100
And now…

101
00:09:33,190 --> 00:09:36,070
We're absolutely pitiful.

102
00:09:38,820 --> 00:09:40,990
We lost Hjalti and yet

103
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:44,660
the two of us are pitifully

104
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:46,500
trying to hang on to life.

105
00:09:49,670 --> 00:09:50,960
And despite that

106
00:09:51,630 --> 00:09:54,010
we're still dreaming.

107
00:10:07,140 --> 00:10:09,310
How are Gardar's wounds?

108
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:11,360
Did he stop bleeding?

109
00:10:16,780 --> 00:10:18,030
The right side of his chest

110
00:10:19,530 --> 00:10:21,120
was bleeding so much.

111
00:10:22,330 --> 00:10:23,870
When I hid him

112
00:10:24,450 --> 00:10:26,870
it was still bleeding.

113
00:10:29,290 --> 00:10:31,250
We don't have much time.

114
00:10:40,050 --> 00:10:41,180
Arnheid…

115
00:10:43,260 --> 00:10:44,510
Are you ready to

116
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:48,270
share the same fate as Gardar?

117
00:10:58,190 --> 00:11:00,990
If you want to
spend your life with Gardar,

118
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:03,450
you'll have to run away with him.

119
00:11:05,740 --> 00:11:08,080
But you are with child.

120
00:11:08,750 --> 00:11:11,250
No doubt, the journey will be difficult.

121
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:15,250
But if you still want to do it,

122
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:18,880
I will help you.

123
00:11:20,630 --> 00:11:21,630
At this point,

124
00:11:22,260 --> 00:11:24,010
that is the only way.

125
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:38,110
The only way, huh?

126
00:11:42,280 --> 00:11:46,240
I will help too. With two people,

127
00:11:46,330 --> 00:11:48,370
maybe we can think of a plan.

128
00:11:49,790 --> 00:11:50,830
Thorfinn…

129
00:12:08,890 --> 00:12:09,810
Ouch!

130
00:12:11,270 --> 00:12:12,480
Don't sleep.

131
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:16,400
The next time you take your eyes
off of Arnheid, I'll break your nose.

132
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:19,530
Yes, I'm sorry.

133
00:12:24,820 --> 00:12:25,820
Who is it?

134
00:12:27,910 --> 00:12:31,830
Um, I should start preparing lunch soon.

135
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:37,380
Take the equipment and make it outside.

136
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:41,590
You're a decoy.
Stay where people can see you.

137
00:12:43,800 --> 00:12:46,470
Yes, I understand.

138
00:12:57,560 --> 00:13:00,820
What a sad situation they are in.

139
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:03,940
Don't you think so, Snake?

140
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:08,950
"Slaves

141
00:13:09,030 --> 00:13:12,950
were destined to become slaves
because they were born inferior."

142
00:13:13,040 --> 00:13:14,910
That is what people say.

143
00:13:15,540 --> 00:13:17,830
As if everyone
was meant to play a certain role.

144
00:13:19,210 --> 00:13:22,340
But I don't think so.

145
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:25,510
Slaves were just unlucky.

146
00:13:25,590 --> 00:13:28,300
It's as simple as that.

147
00:13:29,180 --> 00:13:32,350
If luck wasn't on our side, you and I

148
00:13:32,430 --> 00:13:35,430
may have ended up as slaves ourselves.

149
00:13:36,520 --> 00:13:38,350
So what?

150
00:13:38,440 --> 00:13:40,520
That has nothing to do with this.

151
00:13:41,110 --> 00:13:43,730
Five of our men were killed.

152
00:13:43,820 --> 00:13:46,650
I won't be satisfied
until I kill that bastard.

153
00:13:48,280 --> 00:13:51,490
If I let him get away
with killing my subordinates

154
00:13:51,580 --> 00:13:54,580
I'd have no right
to carry a sword anymore.

155
00:13:59,250 --> 00:14:02,250
Well then, just get rid of your sword.

156
00:14:07,050 --> 00:14:08,430
That sword

157
00:14:08,930 --> 00:14:13,010
is not from around here, that much I know.

158
00:14:13,510 --> 00:14:18,190
I assume you have your reasons
for ending up here.

159
00:14:19,140 --> 00:14:21,810
But unless you get rid of your sword,

160
00:14:21,900 --> 00:14:25,280
you won't be able to
eliminate the root of the problem.

161
00:14:27,030 --> 00:14:29,410
That's enough talking, Gramps.

162
00:14:29,490 --> 00:14:31,870
It's time for old people to take a nap.

163
00:14:34,580 --> 00:14:37,450
I will give you my field.

164
00:14:38,460 --> 00:14:40,330
Cultivate the land

165
00:14:40,420 --> 00:14:42,500
and try growing life.

166
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:46,840
It's much better
than waving around a sword.

167
00:14:50,260 --> 00:14:51,890
I can't

168
00:14:51,970 --> 00:14:54,470
stand or walk anymore.

169
00:14:54,970 --> 00:14:56,770
I will die soon.

170
00:14:57,600 --> 00:15:01,350
Take this chance
to start living a normal life.

171
00:15:03,980 --> 00:15:05,690
I owe you

172
00:15:05,770 --> 00:15:09,530
for having you
read the Bible to me, after all.

173
00:15:13,240 --> 00:15:16,450
Now is not the time for this nonsense.

174
00:15:16,950 --> 00:15:18,950
As if I'd work on a field…

175
00:15:20,830 --> 00:15:22,750
-Boss!
-Huh?

176
00:15:22,830 --> 00:15:24,630
There's somebody there.

177
00:15:28,340 --> 00:15:31,260
Over there. The third tree from the back.

178
00:15:32,510 --> 00:15:35,390
I think that's him
in the shadow of the tree.

179
00:15:39,140 --> 00:15:40,520
All right.

180
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:13,840
They're out.

181
00:16:14,340 --> 00:16:15,260
One horse…

182
00:16:15,760 --> 00:16:19,390
two horses, three horses.
Okay, that's all of them.

183
00:16:23,980 --> 00:16:26,610
I'm counting on you, Einar.

184
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:45,710
Spread out.

185
00:16:46,210 --> 00:16:48,790
Chase him from different
directions and viewpoints.

186
00:16:54,050 --> 00:16:55,380
Old Master!

187
00:16:55,470 --> 00:16:58,680
Sorry, but I'm going to borrow
a horse and wagon.

188
00:16:58,760 --> 00:17:02,680
I promise I will work
and pay you back for it.

189
00:17:03,430 --> 00:17:05,850
Stop worrying about such trivial things.

190
00:17:05,940 --> 00:17:09,150
More importantly,
put me on the wagon as well.

191
00:17:09,230 --> 00:17:11,650
If I'm on it, nobody will question you

192
00:17:11,730 --> 00:17:14,070
while you're on this farm.

193
00:17:14,650 --> 00:17:16,410
No, but…

194
00:17:16,490 --> 00:17:18,620
I can't get you involved in this.

195
00:17:19,870 --> 00:17:22,330
I'm already involved in this.

196
00:17:23,040 --> 00:17:26,540
Stop bickering and help me out already.

197
00:17:28,380 --> 00:17:31,050
Yes. Thank you so much.

198
00:17:35,970 --> 00:17:39,680
That bastard is trying to
escape into the forest.

199
00:17:40,300 --> 00:17:43,470
We can't navigate those woods on horses.

200
00:17:43,560 --> 00:17:45,930
Catch up to him! Don't let him inside.

201
00:17:50,110 --> 00:17:52,480
Damn it! It's so far!

202
00:18:09,750 --> 00:18:10,830
He's still alive.

203
00:18:11,590 --> 00:18:13,130
She did a good job.

204
00:18:14,170 --> 00:18:16,720
But he's as cold as stone.

205
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:19,890
He lost too much blood.

206
00:18:21,140 --> 00:18:23,600
Please hang in there.

207
00:18:28,770 --> 00:18:29,900
He's fast.

208
00:18:30,810 --> 00:18:34,940
No matter how you look at it,
he's not running like a wounded person.

209
00:18:36,490 --> 00:18:38,530
Spider, Badger!

210
00:18:38,610 --> 00:18:40,490
Keep chasing him.

211
00:18:40,990 --> 00:18:42,740
But don't get too close.

212
00:18:43,240 --> 00:18:44,910
If he's Gardar,

213
00:18:44,990 --> 00:18:47,250
you two won't be able to handle him.

214
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:49,670
I'll send backup later.

215
00:18:50,250 --> 00:18:54,000
Until then, keep on chasing him. Got it?

216
00:18:54,590 --> 00:18:55,840
I'm counting on you.

217
00:18:56,590 --> 00:18:59,510
What?! Hey, Boss! Where are you…?

218
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:07,270
The wagon is ready.
Let's rush to the southern border.

219
00:19:08,100 --> 00:19:09,600
Once we're in a different country,

220
00:19:09,690 --> 00:19:12,230
it'll be hard for the guests to chase us.

221
00:19:12,310 --> 00:19:15,150
I'll part ways at some point
as a diversion.

222
00:19:15,230 --> 00:19:17,190
I'll try to lure as many as I can.

223
00:19:18,990 --> 00:19:22,870
Old Master, please accompany us
until the end of the farm.

224
00:19:24,370 --> 00:19:25,830
Understood.

225
00:19:58,230 --> 00:20:00,490
I didn't hear any horses.

226
00:20:04,110 --> 00:20:06,450
He got off his horse and ran here?

227
00:20:12,460 --> 00:20:13,830
I see…

228
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:17,840
He's unconscious, huh?

229
00:20:18,750 --> 00:20:21,590
No wonder I couldn't sense his presence.

230
00:20:28,510 --> 00:20:29,720
Thorfinn…

231
00:20:41,280 --> 00:20:43,070
Just so you know, Thorfinn.

232
00:20:43,950 --> 00:20:45,990
Negotiation is not an option.

233
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:50,950
Hand over Gardar without a fight.

234
00:20:51,700 --> 00:20:53,000
Or else

235
00:20:54,580 --> 00:20:55,540
I'll cut you down.

236
00:21:02,630 --> 00:21:04,130
There are three pursuers.

237
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:07,140
But right now, Snake is the only one here.

238
00:21:07,220 --> 00:21:08,720
I don't sense the other two.

239
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:11,890
If I can somehow stop him,

240
00:21:12,390 --> 00:21:14,310
we can still run away.

241
00:21:15,770 --> 00:21:19,650
Dodge his sword
and land a blow to his chin.

242
00:21:22,780 --> 00:21:24,820
Are you going to fight, Thorfinn?

243
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:28,530
Oh well, I guess it can't be helped
in this situation.

244
00:21:29,030 --> 00:21:31,290
You're genuinely trying to help someone.

245
00:21:31,790 --> 00:21:34,790
You're using your fists for a just cause.

246
00:21:37,370 --> 00:21:39,460
That being said,

247
00:21:40,040 --> 00:21:44,010
your opponent has his own
just cause as well.

248
00:21:44,920 --> 00:21:47,220
What will you do, Thorfinn?

249
00:21:47,720 --> 00:21:50,430
Will you uphold nonviolence regardless?

250
00:21:50,930 --> 00:21:55,230
Or will you fight for the sake of
helping others?

251
00:21:57,940 --> 00:22:01,900
Which one leads to the path
of a true warrior?

252
00:22:02,570 --> 00:22:04,530
There's no time to think.

253
00:22:06,450 --> 00:22:09,110
Look, right in front of you.

254
00:23:13,390 --> 00:23:16,430
You think you can win against him
with your head in the clouds?

255
00:23:48,460 --> 00:23:50,050
What a strange stance.

256
00:23:50,920 --> 00:23:52,760
It's not a spear or an axe.

257
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:54,680
A sword?

258
00:23:57,760 --> 00:23:58,890
No…

259
00:25:54,260 --> 00:25:55,090
''Way Home.''

260
00:25:55,170 --> 00:25:56,470
Subtitle translation by: Kiko Morita

